body:
Flows the time, into the arms of a wheel;
Some painted dark, others in a colourful tint.

Spins the wheel, picking the stowaways;
Some are lost, others guide the way;

Floats the boat, bearing life\u2019s name;
Some learn to enjoy, others worry about being dead.

Shines the light, bright and high;
Though it\u2019s a day, the night isn\u2019t nigh.

For darkness dwindles, even under the clouds;
Nowhere to run, until it has enough prowled.

Learn to perceive, or you might drift away.
Some understand, others take it as play;

It,s a game of chance or a preset bout,
You will never know without a doubt;
Play it with passion, as forfeit isn\u2019t an option.

Live in the moment for you shall not get it again,
Don\u2019t regret what\u2019s been done some other day.
Be it a monochrome or a colourful wine,
Those who know how, always enjoy.
